items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions are generally improvised with some prompts or loose scripting.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. We are also very interested in filming with queer couples, interracial couples, or polycules.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are September 23 through 26, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is 60 cad, duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again.

items.text:
**PAID OPPORTUNITY FOR UK BUSINESS OWNERS!**

Are you a business owner with a captivating story and a knack for on-camera presence? Fancy getting paid to promote your company?

**Casper Black Casting** & **Quickbooks** are seeking **dynamic entrepreneurs** of all sizes to participate in a series of fun and engaging YouTube business-based game shows!

We're looking for business owners, from startup freelancers to those generating seven-figure revenues, who are comfortable discussing and even debating their ventures. This is a fantastic opportunity to pitch your business, share your experiences, and potentially gain valuable exposure.

**What we're looking for:**

*Business Owners of All Types: *From individual freelancers to established businesses with significant revenue.

*Comfortable on Camera*: You'll be the star of the show, so a natural and confident on-screen demeanor is essential. *Memorable personalities are welcome! *We want 10/10 out of the box personalities.

*Willing to Discuss Your Business and Revenue:* Be prepared to openly share insights into your operations and financial journey.

**Shoot Details:**

Location: West London

Duration: Approximately 2-3 hours

Timeframe: Early October (likely 2nd or 3rd October)

If you're ready to showcase your business and your personality, we want to hear from you!

**Please email casper@casperblackcasting.com with the answers to these questions:**
1. We require that you are a business owner. Please specify your annual revenue:
* ¬£0-¬£100k per year
* ¬£100k-¬£1m per year
* ¬£1m+ per year
2. Please describe your business in 1-2 sentences.
3. Kindly detail your previous on-camera experience.
4. Please send a link to your website if applicable.
5. Kindly share your contact number.

We are casting for a role in our feature film ‚ÄòFairy Dust‚Äô!

Please only apply if you fit the brief in the picture and also meet the following criteria:
- Actors must be North Wales based.
- Actors must have the right to work in the UK.
- Actors must be over the age of 18 in real life.
- Must be comfortable wearing full face mask.

Pay is ¬£100 for the day.
Local travel expenses will also be covered & lunch provided.

To apply please send your Spotlight link (or acting CV) as well as your showreel to momentsoffiction@outlook.com

.

# **CASTING CALL!!!!**

**Student Film**

**Non-union**

****PAID****

Hello, I am directing my senior film at the University of Colorado Denver. 

# *Exit Wound*

*One night, one place, one past, two people.*

*Lucy‚Äôs plans for the future unravel when her wounded ex resurfaces, awakening questions and feelings she thought she‚Äôd left behind.*

## *Lucy*

*Female, 22-26, African-American*

*A sharp, ambitious med student is forced to confront old wounds when the man who broke her heart shows up at her door, bleeding and in need.*

## *Christian*

*Male, 22-26, African-American*

*A charming but reckless gangster trying to turn his life around in hopes of a second chance with his lost love.*

**Shoot dates:** Early to** **mid-October 

**Rate:** TBD

****SELF-TAPE Audition** **

Please send a self-tape, resume, and headshot to jenmcfar3@gmail.com. 

*Please submit a self-tape with a couple of different takes.*

**If you have any questions, please contact me at jenmcfar3@gmail.com**

*Male, 22-26, African-American*

*A charming but reckless gangster trying to turn his life around in hopes of a second chance with his lost love.*

**Shoot dates:** Early to** **mid-October 

**Rate:** TBD

****SELF-TAPE Audition** **

Please send a self-tape, resume, and headshot to jenmcfar3@gmail.com. 

*Please submit a self-tape with a couple of different takes.*

**If you have any questions, please contact me at jenmcfar3@gmail.com**

[üéâ](https://emojipedia.org/party-popper)CASTING PAID ROLES FOR PETS AND PET PARENTS [üéâ](https://emojipedia.org/party-popper)

Veteos, a local veterinary video production company, is looking for pets for three specific scenes for social media clips for a veterinary financial company. We will be filming within the next month or so in Denver. W9 and signed release required. All scenes are about 2-3 hours of filming. The roles are below:

**Small Dog for a Spa Day** - ($300) Small dog and their pet parent enjoying a spa day. Pup must be able to lie still with a towel over them and on their head with some accessories (see example photo) to show the ultimate puppy spa day! To be considered, please send a video of your small dog lying in a similar position for 5-10 seconds to me via Facebook messenger. 

**Stuffed Animal Lover Dog** - ($300) Dog who LOVES stuffed animals - any stuffed animal! In this scene, we will be making a stuffy "come to life" with a life-size costume of a provided stuffy. Dog must love any and all stuffies, *even if new to them*. To be considered, please send a video of your dog loving their stuffed animals to me via Facebook messenger. 

**Cat Chasing Laser Pointer** - ($300) Cat who can easily follow and loves playing with a laser pointer with their pet parent. Filming location may be rented home or pet parents home depending on the cat's preference and comfort level.To be considered, please send in a video of your cat actively chasing a laser pointer to me via Facebook messenger. 

I can't wait to see your submission!

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of animal

topComments.text: Where do we send submissions please?
Sent you one of my pup- will be sending the cat one soon too!

items.text: Shailene Woodley (‚ÄûBig Little Lies‚Äú): ‚ÄúI think Tony is absolutely incredible and coming to class for me isn‚Äôt just about letting loose and growing my ability as an actor but more sometimes to really open up myself to the universe and just be. Sometimes I find him saying things that I mentally live by and its so refreshing to constantly hear them being affirmed. Thank you so much for every week re-instilling that positivity and creativity and openness within. You allow me as an actor to forget about the character and remember about Shailene, which makes every movement, moment and word so authentic and true. I‚Äôm so grateful to have you as a mentor.‚Äù

sharedPost.text:
We are casting for a role in our feature film ‚ÄòFairy Dust‚Äô!

Please only apply if you fit the brief in the picture and also meet the following criteria:
- Actors must be North Wales based.
- Actors must have the right to work in the UK.
- Actors must be over the age of 18 in real life.
- Must be comfortable wearing full face mask.

Pay is ¬£100 for the day.
Local travel expenses will also be covered & lunch provided.

To apply please send your Spotlight link (or acting CV) as well as your showreel to momentsoffiction@outlook.com

.

items.text:
Hey everyone üëã I‚Äôve just launched NN5 Talent as part of NN5 Creative Studios. We‚Äôre representing actors, social media content creators, and emerging influencers (18+), especially those from underrepresented backgrounds.

I‚Äôve worked in the industry for over a decade, supporting actors who‚Äôve gone on to projects including Top Boy Season 3 (Channel 4/Netflix), The Play That Goes Wrong (Duchess Theatre), The Queen‚Äôs Shoes (Feature Film), Ladies Day (Sky Arts ShortFlix), Berlin Station (Paramount/Epix), Tyrant (Fox), The Angel (Netflix), Macbeth (BBC), Flesh and Bone (Edinburgh Headliner/Soho Theatre), Gomorrah (Sky Atlantic), Autopsy (ITV), and Banged Up Abroad (National Geographic).

If you‚Äôre looking for representation or want to join a creative hub that‚Äôs about real collaboration and growth, check out www.nn5creativestudios.com and drop me an email at create@nn5creativestudios.com.

Let‚Äôs make things happen. üé¨‚ú®

I‚Äôm now offering private professional career guidance for actors/models/voice actors. I will help you navigate through the industry while providing honest and constructive feedback. Helping you build the perfect package to grab the attention of agents, and recommend the best agents to reach out to. I will review all of your materials and help you with creating your reel/clips, choosing your best headshots, laying out your resume, and writing a great introduction. Picking the best images and photographers for your modeling portfolio. Making sure you have your best runway walk and poses. Selecting the best copy for your monologues and VO commercial reels. And helping you pick the best acting class/coach for you. 

I work with all levels of talent. Beginners, children, teens, adults, as well as established talent. We will focus on everything you need/want to focus on. This session is for you!

Please email me for 30/60 minute private professional session rates and special promotions!

items.text:
Thank you so much for welcoming me to your group!  

I'm a NYC and NJ native, now living in Florida, pursuing acting work to support my film project.  I have significant experience in films.  Supported directors and producers.  I had 5 years as an extra for feature films such as El Cantante, Be Kind/Rewind, and traveled to audition for theatre and short films. Beyond acting, I'm an editor, photographer, and former Spectrum Television production intern with five years of hands-on experience with equipment, and in 2019 created my first show in Western Connecticut, Channel 192, "Spoken Voices."  A passionate advocate against domestic violence. I bring dedication, creativity, and authenticity to every role, and you can find me on FaceBook, "Maribel Brooks" for future auditioning!

items.text:
Hi everyone . I‚Äôve not posted in groups in a long time . I took a break from acting full time almost six years ago when I nearly lost my little girl nine times in one year  to an illness. 
I spent those six years, training , making connections and friends. Some directors, producers and writers from the likes of Netflix , Warner Bros, Lionsgate etc and some known actors . I wrote scripts that have now been sold to Lionsgate directors and being read by Pierce Brosnan, Samuel L Jackson and many more . 
I changed my whole outlook on acting and the industry and Instead for the last six years it‚Äôs been my only goal to help as many actors as I possibly can . I‚Äôve self funded features to help get as many actors and crew seen as I can , always circulating new actors and new crew every film. 
I spent the last six years building an acting curriculum and opened The Foundry Acting Studio after I not only exceeded spotlight approval by over three times but the studio is also SAG recognised too and soon to be other organisations. 
I‚Äôve had actors come to my class for three or four weeks and leave other major schools they were training at for three to four years. 

I offer in person. Online and one to ones. Which all information can be found on the page or by messaging The Foundry Page. 

I get it trust me . New acting classes , new showreel offers , new headshot specialists . There‚Äôs always doubt and to be honest what I‚Äôve noticed a lot recently in groups is a lot of hate , a lot of abuse and I‚Äôve seen people being attacked left , right and centre in this industry for posting a headshot or looking work. This industry is an absolutely amazing place , if we all pick each other up. So please keep your hate to yourself . All you‚Äôre doing is commenting and people are never going to work with you if you‚Äôre rude , foul mouthed or ignorant . 

So yes I understand people being weary of new things but I‚Äôm hoping we‚Äôve answered a lot below and again. Like the biggest schools out there.  I am spotlight approved , but I‚Äôm also the only independent studio in the U.K. to be SAG recognised and soon to be more . This proves legitimacy. 

So if you‚Äôre an actor or starting acting and you want real training , check out the post below. Also if you‚Äôre a good person , support other actors and pick people up rather than putting people down. Then you‚Äôll fit perfectly. 

Again . Help each other . Pick each other up. Support each other and be kind to each other . Show new actors that the industry can be a wonderful place . 

Also ‚Ä¶. We are the only acting studio making full industry professional feature films and we cast from our students. 

So message us now ‚Ä¶.. hope to meet a lot of you soon and keep being fantastic and pushing for that dream

üé¨ The Foundry Acting Studio üé¨

Train. Work. Belong.

Where world-class coaching meets real screen credits.

At The Foundry, we don‚Äôt do hype, we do results. 

üìöOur coach is an internationally trained actor who paused his own career for five years to build a rigorous, modern curriculum from the ground up. (For the record: the world‚Äôs best acting coaches aren‚Äôt always front-of-camera stars, coaching and acting are different crafts. Ours happens to do both, and he‚Äôs now stepping back on set while leading this programme.)

‚úÖÔ∏èVerified. Recognised. Trusted.
 ‚Ä¢ Spotlight-approved training (and then some). When Spotlight reviewed our curriculum, it exceeded their requirements by roughly three times.
 ‚Ä¢ SAG-recognised. We‚Äôre one of very few independent UK studios to be both Spotlight-approved and SAG-recognised, with more professional bodies in progress.
 ‚Ä¢ Our curriculum has been reviewed by established actors, directors, producers and casting directors. Their feedback is consistent: ‚ÄúThis is the calibre you‚Äôd expect from a major, prestigious franchise school.‚Äù

‚úÖÔ∏èTraining that turns into work
 ‚Ä¢ We own our kit: RED cinema cameras, top-tier lenses, pro-grade sound, the works. No hired ‚Äúshowreel days.‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ We produce our own professional features and shorts and cast from our students.
 ‚Ä¢ Speaking roles guaranteed in our in-house features/shorts for committed students who complete the pathway, because the goal isn‚Äôt just growth; it‚Äôs getting you working.

‚úÖÔ∏èAccessible. Supportive. Serious.
 ‚Ä¢ ¬£100 every four weeks for in-person classes or online classes.
 ‚Ä¢ We also offer one-to-one's intensives to go deeper, faster.
 ‚Ä¢ We welcome beginners, returners and working actors, and all different backgrounds. Whether you‚Äôre on a pension, benefits, full-time or part-time work, we‚Äôve designed this to be accessible and judgment-free. No nepotism. No gatekeeping. Just craft.

üé•Why actors choose The Foundry Acting Studio 
 ‚Ä¢ Curriculum: far beyond the minimum, Spotlight-approved √ó3.
 ‚Ä¢ Pathways: SAG-recognised, with additional organisations pending.
 ‚Ä¢ Industry connection: active relationships with professionals who‚Äôve worked across Netflix, Warner Bros., Lionsgate, FX, HBO, and more.
 ‚Ä¢ Outcomes: high-level training plus on-set experience and speaking roles in our productions.

üì¢What actors are saying
 ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúFour weeks here taught me more than two years at one of the North‚Äôs biggest schools.‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúAfter one 1-to-1 session, I left the class I‚Äôd attended for 18 months, the difference was night and day.‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúI moved from another ‚Äòtop‚Äô school after four weeks at The Foundry, no comparison.‚Äù

üìöWhat you get with usüìö
 ‚Ä¢ High-level curriculum which has taken five years to perfect.
 ‚Ä¢ Spotlight-approved curriculum, SAG-recognised pathways.
 ‚Ä¢ Guaranteed speaking roles in our in-house shorts/features (for students who complete the pathway).
 ‚Ä¢ Professional sets with RED cameras, cinema lenses, and pro sound.
 ‚Ä¢ ¬£100/4 weeks, in-person + online, with optional one-day intensives.
 ‚Ä¢ A community that‚Äôs welcoming, motivating and serious about your future.

‚ú®Ô∏èReady to forge your craft and your career?‚ú®Ô∏è

Join The Foundry Acting Studio.

Contact us for more information 
üìß Info@thefoundryactingstudio.com

**Paid Studio Gig ‚Äì Surrey, BC (1‚Äì2 days, max 7 hrs/day)**

Hey Vancouver actors! We‚Äôre producing a batch of short videos for our brand (YouTube, Reels, TikTok, Facebook) and are looking for a confident on-camera presenter to record with us at our Surrey studio.

**What it is:**
* 1‚Äì2 studio days, max **7 hours per day**
* Scripted teleprompter reads + a few simple pickups/B-roll
* We provide the studio, teleprompter, and all gear
* **Contract provided** and **payment in full on wrap**

**You:** Comfortable on camera, friendly, clear delivery, can self-report to Surrey.

**Dates/Rate:** negotiable and flexable 

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this form, https://form.jotform.com/252610493666057 

with:
* Headshot + reel/links
* Your availability in **[date range]**
* A quick note confirming you can get to Surrey

Thanks! Excited to meet some local talent.

Also need an extra for a few hours who is Asian. ( Sept or Oct)

It's a 1-day shoot for approximately 2 hours in Colorado Springs in Oct. . (Also this may turn into a bigger role and would need you more days).

Please send headshot, reel and resume if you have one to daviskathy021@gmail.com.

Imdb credit and reel will be provided. 

More details once picked.  Thank you.

items.text:
Hello all, this is another post for a different student film happening on Auraria Campus. I am not involved in this one, I am posting to this group for the producer since he is not on Facebook. So if you are interested in this one please contact the producer. 

Producer- Brennan Jones bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Production Title- The Cost of Greed 

Production Dates- Exact dates are not set but filming will be in October 

Logline- Peter and Henry are sent on a treasure hunt to a house that is believed to be abandoned. Where they then discover it's not a treasure hunt after all and they must face their greed. Either take the treasure or leave empty handed. 

Peter (19-25) Male 

Peter has a moral compass that he deals with during this film. He wants to do the right thing and in the end that pays off for him. 

Henry (19-25) Male 

Henry is a billionaire with no need for more money, however that does not stop him from thinking he needs more. He is corrupt and in the end karma gets to him. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union.

Contact Email- bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Must contact the producer to be consider for the role. Once you contact Brennan he will send you the audition material.

items.text:
Hello, we are currently casting for a student film on Auraria Campus! 

Producers- Isabella Coronado & Alanagh Finken 

Production Title- Normal Activity 

Production Dates- We don't have exact dates yet but we do know that we are filming in October. 

Logline- A mocumentary following a college's ghost hunting group as they prepare to explore a haunted local brewery's basement where a spirit has resided for the past thirty years. 

Alex (19-25) Male 

Alex is the leader of the ghost hunting group, he is very enthusiastic. He is clearly the one that is most devoted to this group. 

Chelsea (19-25) Female 

Chelsea is your typical girly girl likes being on camera but does not care about the club she is in. She is pretending to so that the club can get funding for the "haunted (not haunted) hot springs". 

Tommy (19-25) Male 

Tommy is very clearly apart of the club because he has eyes for Chelsea, he could not care less otherwise. 

Vera (19-25) Female 

Vera is Alex's sister and is only there because Alex believes they needed a fourth member and basically bribed Vera to join by saying she could borrow his car whenever she wants. 

Gary (45-55) Male 

Gary is the nightwatchmen for the brewery basement. He is very encouraging to Alex with his ghost hunting group. However that encouragement is not for reasons you think, Gary has a secret. 

Documentarian (20-30) Male, Female, Non Binary 

The documentarian is not really shown on camera, however they play a very important role. They are the voice we hear throughout the film asking questions to our characters, and making sarcastic and humorous remarks because they like everyone except Alex, thinks this club is utterly ridicules. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th 

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape 

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union. 

**Contact Email- afinken1@msudenver.edu | icoronad@msudenver.edu **

**You must email both producers. Email the producers about your interest in the role and then we will send you the audition piece for your self tape. You must email to be considered, Facebook Messages does not count. **

Casting Call ‚Äì Mandlig skuespiller/statist s√∏ges

Vi er et hold p√• seks studerende fra VIA Film & Transmedia i Aarhus. I forbindelse med et skoleprojekt samarbejder vi med designer Fie Nielsen og hendes studie, Fj√∂r Studio, om branding af en ny t√∏jkollektion.

Kollektionen udforsker, hvad det vil sige at v√¶re mand i dag, og leger med udtryk, der udfordrer de traditionelle forestillinger om styrke, f√∏lelser og identitet.

Vi s√∏ger en mand i alderen 17‚Äì30 √•r, ca. 180 cm h√∏j, almindelig af bygning og med t√∏jst√∏rrelse small‚Äìmedium.

Praktisk info
 Optagelserne finder sted i Skanderborg

En h√•befuld, men overset filminstrukt√∏r f√•r chancen i en branche styret af sequels og profit ‚Äì og m√• v√¶lge mellem at g√• p√• kompromis med sine v√¶rdier eller med sin karriere.

**CASTING-AUFRUF ‚Äì UGC-Videodreh f√ºr Immobilienprojekt in Heidelberg // Donnerstag 25.09.2025**
 
Drehort: Heidelberg // Bahnstadt

Drehtag: 25.09.2025 - 10.00 Uhr
 
Geplanter Drehzeitraum: halber Drehtag (4‚Äì5 Stunden)
Schauspielhonorar: 500 ‚Ç¨ pauschal
Was wir drehen:

F√ºr unseren Kunden, einen Immobilienunternehmen aus Hamburg, produzieren wir 25 kurze UGC-Videos (User Generated Content) f√ºr Social Media & Online-Ads. Die Videos sind authentisch gesprochene Clips, die direkt in die Kamera eingesprochen werden ‚Äì klar, sympathisch, ruhig.

Skriptl√§nge pro Video: 40‚Äì60 Sekunden, ein Teleprompter ist vor Ort ‚Äì keine Auswendiglernerei notwendig.
 
Gesucht werden:
* 1 Schauspielerin & 1 Schauspieler
* Alter: 28‚Äì40 Jahre
* Look: authentisch, gepflegt, urban-professionell ‚Äì ein nat√ºrlicher ‚ÄûYoung Professional‚Äú-Vibe (Think: Start-up, Immobilienberater, Creator mit Vertrauensausstrahlung)
* Sprache: Hochdeutsch, sichere Sprechweise, gute Artikulation
* Erfahrung mit Kamera & Social Media Ads von Vorteil, aber keine Voraussetzung
√úber uns:

Wir sind die IMMO 4.0 GmbH, ein Performance-Marketing-Unternehmen aus Heidelberg.

Wir entwickeln Marketingkampagnen f√ºr Immobilienvertriebe, Bautr√§ger und Kapitalanlageprodukte im DACH-Raum ‚Äì und setzen dabei bewusst auf echtes, greifbares Storytelling mit professionellem UGC-Content.

Das bieten wir Dir:
* 500 ‚Ç¨ Pauschalgage
* Teleprompter + eingespielte Crew vor Ort
* Styling & Text-Input durch uns (kein Kost√ºm notwendig, clean/professionell reicht)
* Reelf√§hige Referenz f√ºr Deine Mappe
* Zusammenarbeit mit erfahrenem Videoteam in lockerer, produktiver Atmosph√§re

Bewerbung:

Bitte sende uns bis asap Deine Bewerbung mit:
* 2‚Äì3 aktuellen Bildern oder Showreel
* Kurzprofil (Name, Alter, Standort)
* Optional: Link zu Instagram / Agenturseite / Eigenen Reels
* Betreff: ‚ÄûUGC-Videodreh Heidelberg ‚Äì Vorname Nachname‚Äú

Bewerbung bitte per WhatsApp an: +49 172 7042469

(Phillip Kirillov - IMMO4.0 GmbH)

Hinweis:

Die finalen Produktionen erscheinen im Rahmen einer Online-Marketingkampagne f√ºr den Bereich Kapitalanlage-Immobilien. Seri√∂s, hochwertig, glaubw√ºrdig.

Wir freuen uns auf Deine Bewerbung ‚Äì let‚Äôs create!

Dein Team von IMMO 4.0 GmbH

items.text:
LOOKING FOR 2 MEN (preferably BASS or BARITONE), 1 WOMAN (preferably ALTO) who can dance and have the ability to harmonize, for our upcoming Holiday Show. 

Ensemble Stage is a professional theater located in Banner Elk, NC which is situated in the Blue Ridge Mtns. in western North Carolina. Our facility consists of over 8000 sq. ft. which includes a 99-seat performance auditorium.

About 90 total hours (rehearsals + performances), no two-show days, no 10-out-of-12's, no more than 3 performances per week (7 total performances). 

contract runs 11/14 thru 12/20.  Fyi- we have no rehearsals Wednesday thru Saturday of Thanksgiving week so you have an opportunity to go be with family if you choose. 

Pay is $260 per week for five weeks (comes to around $14 per hour of actual rehearsal and performance time). Housing is fully provided(includes full kitchen, washer/dryer, wifi, free parking, individual bedroom, no more than two share a bathroom (but usually private) , etc.  Also, no smoking, and no pets (or service animals) are allowed in any housing. 

Round-trip travel reimbursed at $0.25 per mile

Finally,since we are located in the mountains, and since Ensemble Stage does not have a "company car" available for use, having your own vehicle while here is pretty much a necessity. There really is no such thing as walking to the store or to the theatre.

If interested please respond to info@ensemblestage.com, subject- CMAS AUDITIONS. I will then send you details and parameters for you to prepare a video callback audition to be submitted.

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Callum Foley 24, an actor based in Nottingham. I‚Äôve recently been working on background and student film projects, and I‚Äôm keen to get involved in short films, indie projects, and commercials to build on-screen experience.

I‚Äôm currently training at Nottingham Actors Workshop and working towards joining **Spotlight**, so I‚Äôm looking to create footage that will form my first professional showreel.

I have professional headshots available and would be happy to send them over if you have a role I could be suitable for. I‚Äôm based in Nottingham but happy to travel for projects.

You can reach me at **callumfoley1000@gmail.com**.

Thanks,

Hey guys, I'm running a taster session for the screen acting class this Friday for only a fiver! 

In the session, you'll get to practice on a given scene over a couple of takes and I'll also go through the three programs of this autumn: 
* Screen acting drop-in 
* Screen acting Monthly workshop (over 4weeks) to develop presence and get confident on camera. 
* The directing actors Workshop with the last monday of each month with actors in the room! 
* More info at interactors.co.uk @ : info.interactors@gmail.com Make sure you book the ticket for friday via the website if you wish to come! Looking forward to seeing you there!  whttps://www.instagram.com/p/DOeaxfCDLI_/?igsh=MWU0ZHg5aGh5cmI0OQ==

üé≠ADVERT CASTING BRIEFüé≠

Looking for the below Actors:

* 1 x Businesswoman, white, 40s, fit, redhead (banker vibes) - send a 30 sec video speaking Posh English Accent 

* 1 x Businessman, white, 40s, blonde (banker vibes) - Send 30 sec video speaking posh English accent 

* 1 x white woman to be the Driver, 20s (non-speaking)

* 5 x Japanese men, 30s ‚Äì 60s (attractive, good looking) - send a 30sec video reacting and ‚Äúsounding‚Äù Japanese

* 1 x Japanese woman, 20s (non-speaking)

* 2 x White men, late 40s (successful businesspeople, but outdoorsy types. Strapping men) - send a 30 sec video speaking Good Australian accent. ‚Äì ‚ÄúYeah mate!‚Äù

* 1 x Black man (Driver), 40s/50s

* 2 x Indian women, 1 x 30s/40s and 1 x 50s. English speaking - send 30sec video speaking English in authentic Indian/Mumbai accent

* 1x Indian man, 30s. English speaking. - send a 30 sec video speaking English in authentic Indian accent
* 2 x Arab men, 30s & 40s (groomed facial hair ‚Äì beards don‚Äôt have to be long or bushy ‚Äì the current trend is quite short and well-shaped) - send a 30 sec video speaking English but with a natural Saudi / Arab / Gulf accent

* 2x Arab men (non-speaking)

* 2 x Italian men, 40s and 50s (dashing or handsome) - send 30sec video speaking good Italian.

* 1 x Italian woman, 30s (striking or attractive) - send a 30sec video speaking good Italian 

* 1 x Portuguese man 40s (darker-haired ‚Äì maybe a curl, warmer/olive-skinned, maybe dense facial hair‚Ä¶ a Mediterranean vibe) - send a 30sec video speaking Portuguese and English

* 1x Black South African man, 40s (charismatic businessman vibe, the air of trust and success) - Send a 30sec video speaking good English

* 1 x Portuguese woman, 30s + 1 x Black South African woman, 30s  (non-speaking)

* 1 x French man, white, 40s (mischievous, urban, effortlessly stylish, and slightly romantic‚Ä¶ a sense of refinement, wit, and nonchalant charm) - send a 30sec video in Good French accent ‚ÄúC‚Äôest magnifique!‚Äù

* 1 x Chinese man 50s/60s (professional-looking guy. Well-groomed) - send a 30sec video in a distinct Chinese accent

- Speaking Role: Rate is R4000
- Non-Speaking Role: Rate is R2000

DEADLINE: WEDNESDAY (17/09/2025) at 5pm. 

Thank you 
LJ Talent Casting üí´

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

Rob and I are excited to offer another On Camera Experience for the fall!

6 Classes
October 7th - November 11th 
Tuesdays, 6:30 PM until roughly 9:30 PM
$475 per person (that‚Äôs only $80 per class!)

Class Outline
Class One: Getting to know each other, on camera terms and techniques
Class Two: Commercials
Class Three: Comedy
Class Four: Drama
Class Five: Video Games
Class Six: ‚ÄúOn Set‚Äù - a professional camera op will be filming this class. 

Classes will be a mix of on-camera acting technique and scene study with some acting feedback. All raw footage will be filmed and shared with the students.

Hope you can be a part of it!

CASTING MONOLOG ‚Äì bei Interesse findet am 06. Und 07 November in Berlin ‚Äì auf  der Probeb√ºhne ein Arbeiten mir statt. Bitte melden per e-mail oder Nachricht!

Musik - Schwenk auf ein Sofa oder Bett. Die Schauspielerin erhebt sich aufreizend l√§chelnd:

*Meine Herren ‚Äì Ihr M√§chtigen dieser Erde ‚Äì ein jeder Mann erwartet sich ein Fest ‚Ä¶ mit mir‚Ä¶*

Musik - √úberblendung

Die SCHAUSPIELERIN, in einem d√ºnnen seidenen Neglig√© gekleidet, in ihrer K√ºnstlergarderobe ‚Äì sie schminkt sich, betrachtet die Papierkrone, die auf dem Schminktisch liegt: ‚Ä¶..*ja ja*‚Ä¶.*mit mir‚Ä¶*

Die SCHAUSPIELERIN schenkt sich einen Schluck Vodka ein, raucht eine Zigarette zu Ende.  Die SCHAUSPIELERIN betrachtet sich lange im Spiegel ‚Äì Tr√§nen in den Augen:

*‚Ä¶ und‚Ä¶die M√§chtigen dieser Erde waschen verlogen ihre H√§nde in Unschuld ‚Ä¶..Wir haben es nicht gewollt. Eine bitterb√∂se Ironie‚Äú*

Musik Ende ‚Äì √úberblendung. Die SCHAUSPIELERIN geht einen langen dunklen Gang entlang. An der einen Wand Bilder von M√§chtigen M√§nner: Trump, Putin, Xi, Ghandi, Hitler, Ben Gurion, usw. Auf der anderen Gangseite Bilder von bekannten Frauen der Weltgeschichte. Musik - √úberblendung auf leere B√ºhne ‚Äì Die SCHAUSPIELERIN in einem bodenlangen Mantel, auf dem Kopf die goldene Papierkrone, grell geschminkt, stark rote Lippen, wei√üumrandete Augen - in einem Lichtkegel:

*‚Ä¶doch gebt mir ein K√∂nigreich als B√ºhne, Prinzen f√ºr die Schauspieler ‚Äì und ein Haus voller Monarchen! Wie stellt man sonst einen so stolzen Vorwurf dar, wie die Geschichte von Euch - M√§chtigen? Meine Herren - Verzeiht ‚Äì wenn Ihr es schafft, dass schon ein kleiner Tintenklecks auf einem blo√üen St√ºck Papier den Wert einer Million bestimmen kann ‚Äì so lasst uns fadenscheinige Kom√∂dianten f√ºr heute den verwegenen Versuch, als Nullen der gewaltigen Totale auf eure Fantasie zu wirken!*

Musik - √úberblendung

Die SCHAUSPIELERIN:

*Ja - mit Eurer Fantasie stellt Euch Armeen vor! Und macht aus einem Manne tausend! Doch wenn ich ‚ÄûPferde‚Äú sage, seht sie, Seht! Da sind sie! Seht sie traben, diese Pferde! Seht ihre Hufe in die weiche Erde schlagen!*

*Meine Herren - nur eure Gedanken sind¬¥s, die meine K√∂nige in Gold und Purpur kleiden m√ºssen, sie hin und her versetzen. Nur Eure Fantasie springt √ºber Zeiten weg und kann den Lauf von Jahren umdrehen, wie ein Stundenglas.*

*Bildet Euch ein, da w√§ren tausend Schiffe! Und seht wie m√§chtig ihre Brust sich durch den stolzen Schaum des Meeres bricht, vom unsichtbaren Wind gejagt!*

*Und seht den flinken Burschen dort mit seiner Lunte!*

*Jetzt z√ºndet er die teuflische Kanone- und alles bricht vor Euch zusammen!*

*Und weiter! Versetzt euch wie ein Blitz aufs Schlachtfeld!*

*Seht meine Schwerter tanzen und sich in eurer Feinde Brust versenken!*

*Ja, sie sind aus Blech und schadhaft, l√§cherlich. Aber sie tanzen nicht zum Spa√ü: die Schlacht ist ernst, wahrhafter als die Wirklichkeit! Ich bitte aber den Historiker unter Ihnen ‚Äì in aller Demut - die Daten, Zahlen und die Fakten nicht mit dem Ma√üstab der exakten Wissenschaft zu messen. Die Geschichte von Euch m√§chtigen Herren l√§sst sich nicht erz√§hlen.  Nur in ihrer Ganzheit ist sie wahr, und wo sie wahr ist, ist sie nicht exakt! Denn nichts erhebt sich von der Erde, dass nicht die Zeit mit ihrer Sichel niederm√§ht! Im Gegenteil‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ich baut vor Eurer T√ºr ein Weidenh√ºttchen und s√§nge Lieder ‚Äì laut - der Liebe! Und wenn die Musik der Liebe Nahrung - so spiel ich weiter, weiter bis zum √úberdruss. Meine Herren - Ihr M√§chtigen dieser Erde: Schie√üt nicht auf mich Kom√∂diantin!*

Mit einem L√§cheln verbeugt sich die SCHAUSPIELERIN ‚Äì dann pl√∂tzlich ein Schuss.  Die SCHAUSPIELERIN sinkt langsam zu Boden. Blackout.

items.title: CASTING MONOLOG ‚Äì bei Interesse findet am 06. Und 07 November in Berlin ‚Äì auf  der Probeb√ºhne ein Arbeiten mir statt. Bitte melden per e-mail oder Nachricht!

items.text:
Ich suche 1-3 Mitstreiter f√ºr ein Stra√üentheaterprojekt, egal ob Anf√§nger, erfahrene Amateure oder Profis.

Das St√ºck (zwischen 2:30 und 15:00 Minuten) soll gemeinsam anhand unserer individuellen F√§higkeiten (zB Tanz, Musik, Akrobatik) entwickelt werden. Grobe Konzepte habe ich schon erarbeitet, genau so wie ich schon einen rechtlichen Rahmen abgekl√§rt habe.

Mir ist dabei wichtig, dass es humorvoll zugeht, Gag auf Gag w√§re ein zentraler Punkt meines Vorstellung, gern gepaart mit einer anachronistischen Optik.

Erfahrung und M√∂glichkeit im Bereich B√ºhnenbau und technischer Umsetzung ist reichlich vorhanden.

Ihr solltet in der Umgebung von Aachen wohnen, um regelm√§ssige Proben m√∂glich zu machen.

Neben dem Interesse am Spielen m√∂chte ich den finanziellen Aspekt nicht ganz aussen vor lassen, ich k√∂nnte mir langfristig vorstellen, hier einen relevanten Teil meines Einkommens zu bestreiten. Ziel ist zun√§chst das guerilliam√§ssige Auftreten in Fu√üg√§ngerzonen, sp√§ter auch die Teilnahme an internationalen Festivals in Deutschland, Belgien und Frankreich.

Das Ganze soll wirklich langfristig angelegt sein, gern √ºber mehrere Jahre.

Die Fotos habe ich mal angeh√§ngt, um ganz grob zu zeigen, in welche Richtung es gehen k√∂nnte.

Ich freue mich √ºber alle Anfragen.

Dato: Mandag 22. September

‚ÄºÔ∏èNORTHWEST BIPOC ENTERTAINERS‚ÄºÔ∏è

We are actively seeking talented BIPOC performers to bring beloved characters such as; Princess Tiana, Mulan, Mirabel, Jasmine, Moana, iconic Korean figures and more to life through engaging and authentic performances.

To our company representation matters! We are committed to celebrating the rich cultural heritage of these characters embodied by casting performers who reflect their backgrounds. Whether you're an experienced entertainer or a passionate newcomer, if you have a love for storytelling, performance, and creating magical moments for audiences of all ages, we invite you to join us in inspiring the next generation through inclusive and empowering portrayals.

Please PM Ever Enchanted Events or email everenchantedevent@gmail.com with a headshot, CV and a little about yourself and your backgroundü•∞‚≠êÔ∏è
